QUERY PARAMETERS
----------------

https://sfg-beer-works.github.io/brewery-api/#tag/Beer-Service

beer supporting scenarios:
 - by name
 - by style
 - by name and style
 - no params

Order:
- define test (IT) (TDD) - testListBeersByName() - with mockMvc, give it queryParam
- controller - update listBeers to accept a new @RequestParam for beerName
  - fix tests
- prefer to implement checking logic inside service
- service - update listBeers to accept parameter and do extra checks
  - can use IntelliJ to refactor/change-signature, so it will fix all places. Do it in the interface ..
- repository - define own findAllByXXX (findAllByBeerNameIsLikeIgnoreCase) ..
  - define new test for repo
  - deoarece folosim test-splice (@DataJpaTest), or sa fie 0 records
  - no data from DB - so do import of BootstrapData AND the implementation (annotated class)..
      @DataJpaTest
      @Import({BootstrapData.class, BeerCsvService.class})
      class BeerRepositoryTest

Notes:
- JPA support combining AND for multiple fields: findAllByXXX, findAllByYYY => findAllByXXXAndByYYY

Q: When implementing a query method on a Spring Data Repository interface, do you need to provide the implementation?
   No, you do not need to provide the implementation. You only need to follow the naming conventions to achieve the desired query behavior.



